- which version of caravel you are using
- what you are doing and what you get, if it's an error please post the backtrace from the log

@dennisobrien - I'll have a chance to take a better look closer to the end of the week.
Thanks for the detailed stacktraces and scripts.

We are using caravel with mysql and passwords in our production. Looks like the issue is that somehow `def pre_add(self, db):` isn't executed in your case.

@dennisobrien  If you are going to poke with testconn please cherry-pick whatever seems sensible (the test at least) from this pull request:
https://github.com/airbnb/caravel/pull/694

Also my logic in views seems a bit easier to follow i think.
